707565f-a.text:
First Avenue, east side, from E. 32nd (right) to 33rd (left) Streets, showing a gasoline station occupying this entire frontage.
View No. 2 sows a portion of the preceding view (the N.E. corner of Firs Avenue and E. 32nd Street, between First Avenue and the East River. In this instance the photographer is viewing southeastward.

712018f-a.text:
East 32nd St. west from (No. 327, 4 story structure at right) a point midway between 1st and 2nd Aves. and across the latter. Underneath this street surface is a tunnel of the Pennsylvania Railroad connecting the terminal at 7th Ave. ( and barely observable in the distance of the view) with long Island. Note the Empire State building across the roof tops of the buildings on the north side of this thoroughfare

May 8, 1938.

P.L. Sperr.
